> > I have a small engine analyzer that measures
> 'point resistance'.
> 
> It checks how good the connection from the points to
> ground is.
> 
> From the web, "Turn the engine over until the points
> are closed and then use
> an ohmmeter to connect the meter to the primary
> point lead and to ground. If
> resistance reading is too high, the points are
> burned and must be replaced".
